article_title: Federal government releases health insurance exchange costs for Floridians - Sarasota News
article_text: A cool front will stall to our south and keep our wind out of the northwest. This will allow our dewpoints and humidity to drop a bit. Temperatures will still be warm in the afternoon. There is a chance for early sprinkles but the day will be mostly dry by midmorning and beyond.

og.description: SARASOTA - The U.S. Department of Health and Human Services released a report Wednesday on premium costs within the new, online health insurance exchange.
